Notes. A South American species, found throughout the continent, but no records from Central America. This is one of few Neotropical Platypodinae species that are considered as pests; it kills trees in plantations, primarily poplars, both in the southern part of its native range and where introduced in Europe (
Tremblay et al . 2000
;
Girardi et al . 2006
;
Alfaro et al . 2007
).
